args: What is it you seek to show me?
Hee hee! You'll just have to wait and see.\nC'mon, it's this way!
Lessee... Last year it was over...here?
Hmph! Go ahead and cryâ€”I'm not sorry!
Looks like a couple siblings are going at it.\nProbably nothing serious.
(And since she's actually down to help,\nI better step the heck up!)
On it, girl! I'll get 'em sorted.
I wonder if she's really the best\nto handle this...
Hey, squirts. What's with the waterworks?
He promised we'd eat kebabs together at\nthe festival, but then he ate ALL of 'em!
I think you owe your little sis here\nan apology, hungry man.
Nuh-uh! I knocked on her door like a\nBAZILLION times this morning and she\nnever answered, so it's her own fault!
I waited for her until noon! If I waited any\nlonger, the kebabs mighta been gone!
Wait, she stood you up until past noon?!\nNOT cool, dudette!
Girl, you are mad killing me here.\nWhat's your deal?
See? I told you it's your own fault!
Okay, let's take it down a few dozen pegs\nwith the blame talk. I'm sure your sister\nhere had her reasons for the ditch.
Work with me, girl. Stop crying for a\nsec and break it down for us.
Oh man, big yikes. I feel like I\njust made things worse.
Um, wait! Kebabs! You missed out,\nso I'll just buy you a new one!
You can split it with your bro\nand we'll all call it gooâ€”
Nooo! That's not the point! I don't want it!
Okay, now I'm SUPER lost.\nAren't you fighting over kebabs?
I fear the seeds of her melancholy\nlie elsewhere.
Do you know something here, Ria?\n'Cause I am WAY outta my element.
Also, are you sure you wanna do this?\nI thought you were keeping everything\non the down-low and stuff.
Doing naught to ease their strife\nwould sit ill upon my conscience.
I would ask you dry your eyes, child.
Calm, little one. You are not at fault here.\nNow prithee, heed my query.
Excellent. Now then, may I assume you\nlooked forward to today's festivities with\ngreat anticipation?
Yeah, I was really, really, REALLY excited.
But you did not attend it straight away,\ninstead staying in your bedchamber past\nmidday. Surely you had reason for such?
Yeah, I couldn't decide what to wear.\nI wanted to look extra pretty 'cause it's\na festival, so I... I...
I just wanted to look cute.
Oh, I vibe hard with thatâ€”sometimes it\ntakes forevs to put together a power look!
B-but he just left me and went off\nall by himself!
And you felt sad, which soon\ngave way to quarrel.
It wasn't the food she really cared aboutâ€”\nit was getting to enjoy the festival with her\nbig bro there.
Then why didn't you just SAY so?!
Aw, it's... Look, I'm sorry, okay?\nI should have waited for you.

Well spoken, child. And now that you have
treated and come to concord, the two of
you may depart and revel in the festival's
delights together.
(Fie, Nadine! I completely forgot\nto mimic your mannerisms!)
(D-don't worry, girlâ€”I don't think these\nkids have any idea that you'reâ€”)
You listened to me and understood why I\nwas sadâ€”just like Queen Nefaria from\nthe legends!
N-nay, child! You are...uh...mad mistaken!\nI am just, like, a commoner or whatever!
Phew! I can but hope that\ndispelled their suspicions.
I must confess, I am gobsmacked a babe\nof her lean years would know my name.
Really? Why? I mean, you're kiiinda...
Kind of what? Speak your mind plain.
Hee hee! You'll see when we get there.\nNow, let's goâ€”for reals this time!
